description:
Application under s73 of the Town and Country Planning Act for: a) minor material amendments; b) removal or variation of conditions and also c) variation to the original S106 (legal) agreement of planning permission ref: P051176 dated 2 May 2006 for the 'erection of a new part 5 storey/part 6 storey building with basement and rooftop plant enclosure, containing a supermarket and mixed commercial space (A1- retail/A2- financial and professional services/A3- restaurants/A4- drinking establishments/A5- takeaways/ B1 - offices/D1 non-residential institutions/D2- assembly and leisure uses) at basement and ground floors; 2,300sq m of office space; 69 flats (thirty seven x 1 bed, twenty four x 2 bed and  eight x 3 bed) (including 35% affordable housing); and raised garden at first floor level.'

A) The minor material changes include:
i)	introduction of a disabled access lift to provide disabled access from St John Street (to the north of the site). This will be the principle disabled access for residents of the intermediate tenure units; 
ii)	plant area added above Blocks A and B. This is that part of the development adjacent to Compton Passage.  (This also includes the addition of a safety rail 2m from the edge of the building);
iii)	block A (office development adjacent to Compton Passage). The glazing approved at first-fourth floors has been extended to ground level;
iv)	other changes have been made to the approved scheme, but are non-material and therefore have not been listed.

B) removal of conditions 11 (historic plaque) and condition 22 (cycle parking); and variation of condition 24 (supermarket floor areas).  

C) variation of the original Section 106 Agreement to remove clauses 9 and 11 (affordable workshop space provision), to amend clause 10 (fit-out of affordable workspace) and to add an obligation in lieu of the provision of on-site cycle parking. 

